The paper deals with secure multiparty computation, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). It also heavily relies on Fourier series and Parseval's identity, which are concepts from information theory (cs.IT). The protocol is based on arithmetic circuits, which are a topic in computer science theory (cs.DS) and circuit complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper introduces a new kind of multiparty computation protocol, which could be considered a contribution to social and information networks (cs.SI).
